21/12/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The Croatian Mine Action Centre (HCR) reported Friday (19 December) that authorities cleared mines from nearly 269 square kilometres of land this year, a rate more than two times faster than planned. The country's mine-clearing initiatives have received financial support from international donors and from domestic funding sources. HCR's statistics show that 24 companies and one NGO have participated in the projects. (HINA - 19/12/03)
